      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error is scoped out for this assessment because the analysis is a quasi-static implicit structural solve using a direct sparse solver (Ansys SPARSE) with tight convergence tolerances (force residual < 1e-4, displacement residual < 1e-6). Implicit direct solvers do not accumulate iterative or time-stepping errors in the manner addressed by this factor. The dominant numerical error source — discretization — is addressed separately under the Discretization error factor. No iterative convergence or time-integration error is applicable to a single-load-step implicit static analysis, and therefore this factor is not meaningful to assess within the scope of this COU."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/factor/ue",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use error is scoped out because the FEA models were constructed and executed exclusively by credentialed simulation engineers at three independent organizations (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) following a pre-specified modeling protocol with mandatory peer review at each stage (geometry import, material assignment, boundary condition application, and results extraction). The protocol was locked prior to any experimental data unblinding, eliminating analyst-driven post-hoc tuning. Inter-analyst variability was explicitly quantified as part of the ensemble comparison and found to contribute < 2% spread across QoIs, which is subsumed within the reported combined uncertainty. Given the controlled, protocol-driven execution environment and the quantified inter-analyst spread, residual use error is not a credibility-limiting factor for this COU and is therefore scoped out of the structured assessment."
    },
