        "description": "Continuum elasto-plastic constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening) for Ti-6Al-4V ELI; contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian. Achieved Gradation 3: constitutive model form supported by published material characterization and validated against independent coupon data."
      },
      "rationale": "The constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening, E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=2.3 GPa for Ti-6Al-4V ELI) is supported by published tensile coupon data from three independent sources in the literature. Screw-rod contact is represented using augmented Lagrangian contact pairs with a friction coefficient of 0.2, consistent with published tribological data for Ti-Ti interfaces under dry conditions. Model form uncertainty is bounded by the coupon-level calibration residuals (<3% on yield stress)."
    },
    {
