        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "All material and geometric inputs derived from traceable measurements or certified material certificates. Achieved Gradation 3: input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (n=1000) with documented probability distributions."
      },
      "rationale": "Geometric inputs (screw outer diameter, pitch, rod diameter, connector geometry) were measured on production hardware using a Zeiss CMM (calibrated, NIST-traceable) with measurement uncertainty < 0.01 mm. Material properties were taken from certified material test reports for the specific lot used in bench testing. Input uncertainty was propagated through the FEA ensemble via Monte Carlo sampling (n=1000 Latin hypercube), yielding combined input uncertainty contributions of < 4% on all QoIs."
